Customer receives order confirmation

- Components:
• Processes: Browse Product, Add to Cart, Place Order, Payment Process, Order Processing
• Data Stores: Product Database, Order Database
• External Entities: Customer, Payment System


5. What is Flow chart? Create a flowchart to make addition of two numbers  
- A Flowchart is a diagram that represents the step-by-step process of solving a problem or performing an algorithm. 
It uses different symbols to show operations, decisions, input/output, and the flow of control.

- Common Flowchart Symbols
• Oval → Start / End
• Parallelogram → Input / Output
• Rectangle → Process / Calculation
• Diamond → Decision
• Arrow → Flow line (direction of steps)

- Flowchart for Addition of Two Numbers

        +--------+
        | Start  |
        +--------+
             |
             v
     +------------------+
     | Input A and B    |
     +------------------+
             |
             v
     +------------------+
     | Sum = A + B      |
     +------------------+
             |
             v
     +------------------+
     | Display Sum      |
     +------------------+
             |
             v
        +--------+
        |  End   |
        +--------+


6. What is Use case Diagram? Create a use-case on bill payment on paytm.  
- A Use Case Diagram is a type of UML (Unified Modeling Language) diagram used to represent how users 
(actors) interact with a system to perform specific tasks (use cases).

• Show the functional requirements of a system
• Identify actors (users or external systems)
• Describe interactions between actors and the system

- Main Components
• Actor – The user or external system interacting with the system
• Use Case – The function or service provided by the system
• System Boundary – The system being modeled
• Relationships – Connections between actors and use cases

- Use Case Diagram for Bill Payment on Paytm

                 +----------------------+
                 |        Paytm         |
                 |                      |
 User ---------> | (Login/Register)    |
                 |                      |
 User ---------> | (Select Bill Type)  |
                 |                      |
 User ---------> | (Enter Bill Details)|
                 |                      |
 User ---------> | (Make Payment)      |
                 |                      |
                 | (Payment Verification)
                 |                      |
 User <--------- | (Receive Confirmation) |
                 +----------------------+

             |
             v
      +-------------------+
      | Payment Gateway   |
      +-------------------+

- Actors

• User – Person paying the bill
• Payment Gateway / Bank – Processes the payment

- Use Cases

• Login / Register
• Select bill type (electricity, mobile recharge, etc.)
• Enter bill details
• Make payment
• Payment verification
• Receive confirmation








